---
import CalculatorLayout from "../../layouts/CalculatorLayout.astro";
import { ObjectStorageCostCalculator } from "../../components/calculators/ObjectStorageCost";
import { DataEgressCostCalculator } from "../../components/calculators/DataEgressCost";
import { StorageReplicationCostCalculator } from "../../components/calculators/StorageReplicationCost";

const title = "S3 Cost Calculator";
const description =
  "Estimate S3-like object storage costs from GB-month storage, request volume, optional egress, and optional replication assumptions. Educational use only.";
---
<CalculatorLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalPath="/calculators/s3-cost-calculator"
  intro="S3-like storage cost usually comes from storage (GB-month), requests, and egress. Some setups also add replication and cross-region transfer costs. This page groups common line items so you can build a realistic monthly estimate."
  examples={[
    "Start with storage + requests, then add egress if you download data, and replication if you copy across regions.",
    "Many workloads are storage-dominated until egress or replication is added.",
    "Use baseline and peak scenarios to avoid underestimating churn or download spikes.",
  ]}
  includes={[
    "Storage + request fee estimate (GET/PUT) using your pricing assumptions.",
    "Optional egress estimate from GB/month and $/GB.",
    "Optional replication estimate from replicated GB/month and $/GB.",
    "Optional storage growth and RPS estimators.",
    "Scenario-based planning (baseline vs peak) in one worksheet.",
  ]}
  excludes={[
    "Retrieval and lifecycle transition fees for archive tiers (model separately).",
    "Provider-specific tiering and region complexity unless you use blended rates or scenarios.",
    "KMS, inventory, analytics, and additional per-feature charges.",
  ]}
  how={[
    "Step 1: estimate storage cost and request fees.",
    "Step 2: add egress if you transfer data out of storage.",
    "Step 3: add replication/copy line items if you move data across regions.",
    "Sum line items to get a monthly estimate.",
  ]}
  faqs={[
    {
      q: "Do request fees matter for S3?",
      a: "They can for millions of small objects or chatty workloads. For large objects with few operations, storage or egress usually dominates.",
    },
    {
      q: "What drives replication cost?",
      a: "Replicated GB/month (changed data), not the total stored dataset size. Estimate replication volume from writes and churn.",
    },
    {
      q: "How do I estimate GB-month for storage?",
      a: "Use average stored GB over the month. If you have daily values, sum them and divide by days in the month.",
    },
    {
      q: "Should I separate storage classes?",
      a: "Yes. If you use multiple classes, compute each class separately or use a blended rate.",
    },
  ]}
  lastUpdated="2026-02-07"
  related={[
    { href: "/calculators/storage-pricing-calculator", label: "Storage pricing calculator (generic)" },
    { href: "/calculators/s3-request-cost-calculator", label: "S3 request cost calculator" },
    { href: "/guides/s3-pricing-explained", label: "Guide: S3 pricing explained" },
    { href: "/guides/s3-replication-cost", label: "Guide: S3 replication cost" },
    { href: "/guides/s3-crr-vs-srr-cost", label: "S3 CRR vs SRR cost" },
    { href: "/guides/estimate-replication-gb-per-month-from-writes", label: "Estimate replication GB/month" },
    { href: "/guides/copy-storage-pricing", label: "Copy storage pricing checklist" },
  ]}
>
  <div class="prose">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">1) Storage + requests</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:8px">
      Use average stored GB for GB-month billing, and add monthly request counts for GET/PUT pricing assumptions.
    </p>
  </div>
  <ObjectStorageCostCalculator client:load />

  <div class="prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2>2) Optional: egress</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:8px">
      If you download data from storage (to the internet or another region/provider), add an egress line item here.
    </p>
  </div>
  <DataEgressCostCalculator
    transferLabel="Egress from storage (GB / month)"
    priceLabel="Egress price ($ / GB)"
    defaultGbPerMonth={500}
    defaultPricePerGbUsd={0.09}
  client:load />

  <div class="prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2>3) Optional: replication</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin-top:8px">
      Replication fees are often driven by changed data copied per month. Estimate replicated GB/month from write volume
      and churn, then apply your $/GB assumption.
    </p>
  </div>
  <StorageReplicationCostCalculator client:load />
  <div class="prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">How to get your inputs</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Inputs</strong>: use billing exports, metrics, or logs to get real counts/GB where possible.</li>
      <li><strong>Units</strong>: convert throughput (Mbps) or rates (RPS) into monthly units when needed.</li>
      <li><strong>Scenarios</strong>: build a baseline and a high-usage scenario to avoid under-budgeting.</li>
      <li><strong>Sources</strong>: Storage metrics, request logs, and cost exports are the best starting points.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Result interpretation</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Identify the dominant driver (storage vs requests vs egress vs replication).</li>
      <li>If requests dominate, consider caching or batching to reduce per-request costs.</li>
      <li>If egress dominates, check CDN or data locality options.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Common mistakes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Using a single average and ignoring peak/incident scenarios.</li>
      <li>Double-counting or missing adjacent line items (transfer, logs, retries).</li>
    </ul>

    

    <h2>Advanced inputs to capture</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Break down storage by class and average GB-month.</li>
      <li>Separate request classes and counts.</li>
      <li>Include retrieval fees for IA or archive tiers.</li>
      <li>Model data transfer and replication separately.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Scenario planning</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Scenario</th>
          <th>Storage GB-month</th>
          <th>Requests</th>
          <th>Egress</th>
          <th>Replication</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Baseline</td>
          <td>Average</td>
          <td>Expected</td>
          <td>Expected</td>
          <td>Expected</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Peak</td>
          <td>High</td>
          <td>High</td>
          <td>High</td>
          <td>High</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Validate after changes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Compare your estimate to the first real bill and adjust assumptions.</li>
      <li>Track the primary driver metric (requests/GB/count) over time.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Next steps</h2>
    <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:0">
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/">Guides</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/calculators/">All calculators</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/calculators/storage-pricing-calculator/">Storage pricing calculator (generic)</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/calculators/s3-request-cost-calculator/">S3 request cost calculator</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/s3-pricing-explained/">Guide: S3 pricing explained</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/s3-replication-cost/">Guide: S3 replication cost</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</CalculatorLayout>
